.TH SINGINE-INSTALL 1 "2026-03-13" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-install \- install the singine launcher, manpages, or selected local tool dependencies
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine install
[\fIsingine\fR|\fIant\fR|\fIxmldoclet\fR]
[\fB--prefix\fR \fIPATH\fR] [\fB--shell\fR \fBbash\fR|\fBsh\fR|\fBall\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Without an explicit subject, installs the
.B singine
launcher under a local prefix, copies all available manpages to that prefix,
and appends PATH and MANPATH exports to the requested shell startup files.
.PP
With
.B ant
as the subject, installs Apache Ant using Homebrew if it is not already
available on
.BR PATH .
.PP
With
.B xmldoclet
as the subject, ensures Maven is available and then downloads the Saxonica
.B com.saxonica:xmldoclet
artifact into
.IR ~/.m2
for use by
.BR ant\ javadoc-xml .
.SH SUBJECTS
.TP
.B singine
Install the singine launcher and bundled manpages.
.TP
.B ant
Ensure Apache Ant is installed, aligned with the Ant-based build expectations
used by SilkPage and Singine core build files.
.TP
.B xmldoclet
Ensure the Saxonica XML doclet jar is present in the local Maven repository,
installing Maven first via Homebrew when required.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --prefix \fIPATH\fR
Installation prefix. Default is
.IR ~/.local .
.TP
.B --shell
Update
.IR .bashrc ,
.IR .profile ,
or both.
.TP
.B --json
Emit install metadata as JSON.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine install
singine install singine --prefix ~/.local --shell bash
singine install ant
singine install xmldoclet
singine install --prefix ~/.local --shell bash
singine install --json
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1),
.BR singine-man (1),
.BR brew (1),
.BR mvn (1)
